HEADWORD: half-baked
<hw>half-baked</hw> <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Insufficiently or
poorly planned or thought out; impractical or unrealistic; <as>as, a
<ex>half-baked</ex> proposal; <ex>half-baked</ex> ideas</as>; -- of
plans, theories, proposals, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Insufficiently cooked; -- of food.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Halfbeak</ent>⟦br⟧
